<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-38-0534 </DOCNO><TEXT>Using the method of X-ray diffraction analysis, the crystal structureof a new phosphide Zr/sub 2/Ni/sub 1-x/P (x=0.52): sp.gr. Pnma, a=13.852(4),b=3.657(2), c=10.213(2) A, d/sub calcd/=6.99 g/cm/sup 3/, Z=8, R=0.044,is determined. The structure belongs to a new type with trigonal-prismaticcoordination of smaller atoms (Ni and P). Coordination polyhedrons ofZr atoms is a pentagonal prism (CN17), Ni and P atoms - a trigonal prism(CN6+3). The parentage of Zr/sub 2/Ni/sub 1-x/P structure with La/sub3/NiGe/sub 2/, Hf/sub 3/P/sub 2/, S/sub 3/Sb/sub 2/ types is considered.The interatomic distances are given.</TEXT></DOC>